## Supabase tables:
- public.users: id serial PK, name text unique, emoji text, sort_order int
- public.locations: id text PK, label text, icon text, color text, bg text, sort_order int
- public.checkins: id serial PK, user_name text, day text, slot text, location_id text FK->locations.id, week_start date, UNIQUE(user_name,day,slot,week_start)

## Rules:
- getCurrentUser() / saveCurrentUser() stay as localStorage (per-device, not shared)
- Add: export function getWeekStart() { const d=new Date(); d.setDate(d.getDate()-d.getDay()); return d.toISOString().split('T')[0]; }
- All DB calls are async
- WeeklyGrid: on mount fetch users+locations+checkins from Supabase. Poll re-fetches only checkins every 3min.
- checkins rows have user_name (not user), location_id (not locationId) — map accordingly in getCheckin()
- saveCheckin: upsert into checkins with onConflict:'user_name,day,slot,week_start', set location_id
- clearCheckin: delete from checkins where user_name,day,slot,week_start match
- Settings: fetch users+locations on mount from Supabase. addUser inserts into users table (name,emoji='👤',sort_order). deleteUser deletes by name. renameUser updates name. addLocation inserts into locations. deleteLocation deletes by id. updateLocation upserts.
- No loading spinners, no error UI — keep it simple
- users array in WeeklyGrid = array of name strings (map from DB rows)
- locations array = array of {id,label,icon,color,bg} objects (map from DB rows, sorted by sort_order)

